{
  "text": "Putative role of PTX3 in atherosclerosis. Norata et al [CITATION_1] showed that HDL3-S1P induces PTX3 expression in endothelial cells through a PI3K/Akt-dependent pathway. Whether this is responsible for antiinflammatory effect of HDL on endothelial cells is still unknown. However, enhanced PTX3 production may contribute to efficient clearance of apoptotic cells and may thereby limit the development of complex atherosclerotic lesions.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2026403"
